	     Nairobi - Kenya's election chief on Wednesday warned leaders of the ruling party and opposition to stop interfering in the organisation of next week's polls. "I am giving a yellow card to all the political leaders in the country. As the referee I want to issue a stern warning to the players of this game on all sides that they should stop all attempts to interfere with the process," he said in a damning press conference after one of his commissioners quit. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  